SIMPLE: polo
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polo
<hw>Po"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Eastern origin; --
properly, the ball used in the game.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A game of
ball of Eastern origin, resembling hockey, with the players on
horseback.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A similar game played on the ice, or on a prepared
floor, by players wearing skates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A game similar to hockey played by
swimmers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Polo
<hw>Po"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., an air or popular
song in Andalucia.]</ety> <def>A Spanish gypsy dance characterized by
energetic movements of the body while the feet merely shuffle or glide,
with unison singing and rhythmic clapping of hands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polonaise</ent>⟦br⟧
